Ride Reoptimization.description: The Reoptimization feature ensures that rides are distributed optimally throughout the fleet over time, reducing customer wait times, reducing the fleet’s overall driving distance, and increasing vehicle availability.
Ride Reoptimization.title: Ride Reoptimization

Matching and Ride Assignment.description: Configure settings that control how rides are matched and assigned to vehicles
Matching and Ride Assignment.title: Matching and Ride Assignment

Driver Experience.description: Set configurations that manage driver app usage
Driver Experience.title: Driver Experience

Dispatch and Routing.description: Configure operational settings that impact route optimization, dispatching preferences, and customer experience
Dispatch and Routing.title: Dispatch and Routing

additionalFields.description: Define which information is displayed in the Driver App for drivers who manually accept rides
additionalFields.title: Ride Offer Information in Driver App

excludeLastName.description: Prevent client last names from being visible in the Driver App and ride data.
excludeLastName.title: Remove client last name

deactivateOnArrive.description: Set if drivers should be deactivated from vehicles upon arriving to Fuel stop points for electric vehicles. Turn on if drivers are expected to leave vehicles while they are being charged.
deactivateOnArrive.title: EV Charging - Deactivate driver upon arrival

dispatchRideImmediately.description: Dispatch future rides upon creation rather than the default of dispatching future rides at the start of pickup windows. Future rides with pickup windows starting in the next 24 hours will be dispatched.
dispatchRideImmediately.title: Dispatch Future Rides Immediately

latestAfterTimeBufferSeconds.description: Future rides will be considered for reoptimization if the start of the pickup window is below the set limit. This setting is only relevant if the the setting to dispatch future rides immediately is turned on.
latestAfterTimeBufferSeconds.title: Future RIde Pickup Window Limit

minimumImprovement.description: Only reoptimize the ride if the difference between the current vehicle ETA and the alternative vehicle ETA is above this value. Use this setting to reoptimize rides only if they provide a significant benefit. For example, reoptimize rides only if the ETA improvement is greater than 3 minutes from the current ETA.
minimumImprovement.title: Required ETA Improvement

etaBufferSeconds.description: Set the ETA below which rides will not be reoptimized. For example, if set to 3 min, a vehicle 2.5 minutes away from the pickup will not be reoptimized.
etaBufferSeconds.title: Minimum ETA Boundary

windowSize.description: Set the amount of drivers that can be offered a ride at one time.
windowSize.title: Wave size

expiryTimeInSeconds.description: Set the amount of time ride assignment offers remain valid for driver with a manual assignment strategy. Note that long expiry times may have a negative impact on customer experience.
expiryTimeInSeconds.title: Ride Assignment Offer Expiry Time

nextState.description: Set the state to which drivers will transition when they are activated to a vehicle. For operations that don't use the Autofleet Driver App, set the value to "Driving". If vehicle locking is triggered from the Autofleet Driver App, set the value to "Activating" or "Driver on the way", but not "Driving".
nextState.title: Driver Activation State

body.description: Set custom text that will be pre-populated in the Driver App SMS field when driver’s initiate a text message to the contact person of the current stop point.
body.title: SMS Prefix Text

clustering.description: Display vehicles that are in a close proximity to one another as clusters in the Autofleet Driver App.
clustering.title: Cluster Nearby Vehicles in Driver App

territoryDisplay.description: Choose whether to display the operational territory in the driver app or highlight the excluded areas.
territoryDisplay.title: Display Territory in Driver App

Territory.description: Define the area of operation with one or more polygons.
Territory.title: Territories

minTimeBetweenBreaks.description: Set the amount of time after which a driver can start another break
minTimeBetweenBreaks.title: Min Time Between Breaks

maxBreakTime.description: Set the maximum break duration. Once this time is reached, the break will end automatically.
maxBreakTime.title: Max Break Time

driverShiftMarginMinutes.description: Match rides to drivers only if the rides can be completed within drivers’ current shifts. Set the value to 0 minutes to enforce the actual shift end time, a value greater than zero to add a positive buffer, and a negative value to add a negative buffer, effectively shortening and lengthening shift durations respectively. Disable the setting by leaving the value blank.
driverShiftMarginMinutes.title: Enforce Driver Shift Durations in Matching

latestDropoffTime.description: Prefer the vehicle with the shortest ETA to the pickup. Optimizes for customer experience.
latestDropoffTime.title: Earliest ETA

distanceDiff.description: Prefer the vehicle to which the shortest distance is added. Optimizes for fleet efficiency.
distanceDiff.title: Minimum driving distance

optimizeFor.description: Determine how the matching algorithm selects the preferred vehicles
optimizeFor.title: Route optimization strategy

passenger.description: Set the maximum amount of time that a stop point can be delayed relative to the first calculated ETA.
passenger.title: Max Drift - Passenger Rides

delivery.description: Set the maximum amount of time that a stop point can be delayed relative to the first calculated ETA.
delivery.title: Max Drift - Delivery Rides

maxStopPointsOnVehicle.description: Set the maximum number of stop points that can be assigned to a vehicle at once. This setting does not limit adding non-ride stop points and does not apply planning routes. If empty, no limit is applied.
maxStopPointsOnVehicle.title: Max Stop Points on Vehicle

interactiveDescriptionText.description: The duration of a passenger ride can be extended up to
the duration of the direct route, but no more than

passenger.description: Set limits for how much time can be added to a passenger ride due to additional rides being pooled. If empty, no limit is set.
passenger.title: Pooling Impact on Ride Duration - Passenger

interactiveDescriptionText.description: The duration of a delivery ride can be extended up to
the duration of the direct route, but no more than

delivery.description: Set limits for how much time can be added to a delivery ride due to additional rides being pooled. If empty, no limit is set.
delivery.title: Pooling Impact on Ride Duration - Delivery

interactiveDescriptionText.description: will be added to pickup stop points,
to each additional pickup at the same location, and
to each additional dropoff at the same location

stopPointAddedTimeSeconds.description: Set how long it takes to complete ride stop points. This time will be added to the stop point ETAs
stopPointAddedTimeSeconds.title: Added ETA Time

maxWaitTimeSeconds.description: Set the amount of time after which drivers can fail passenger rides after arriving to the pickup
maxWaitTimeSeconds.title: Rider No Show

DRIVER_CAN_REQUEST_BREAKS.description: Enable drivers to take breaks in the Autofleet Driver App
DRIVER_CAN_REQUEST_BREAKS.title: Driver App Breaks

MIN_TIME_BETWEEN_BREAKS_MILLI.description: Set the amount of time after which a driver can start another break
MIN_TIME_BETWEEN_BREAKS_MILLI.title: Min Time Between Breaks

MAX_BREAKS_PER_SHIFT.description: Set the maximum amount of breaks a driver can take in a single shift
MAX_BREAKS_PER_SHIFT.title: Max Breaks Per Shift

MAX_BREAK_TIME_MILLI.description: Set the maximum break duration. Once this time is reached, the break will end automatically.
MAX_BREAK_TIME_MILLI.title: Max Break Time
